	"description": "In React, data is typically passed down from parent to child via props. But this\ncan lead to &quot;prop drilling&quot; – where we have to pass props down through lots of\ncomponents to get them where they&#x27;re needed.\n\nAlso, some props (for example, the current authenticated user, UI theme, or\npreferred language) will be required by many components within an application.\n\nReact&#x27;s Context API provides a way to share values like these between components\nwithout having to explicitly pass them down as a prop thr",
